There is nothing more demoralising than a small but inadequate income – Edward Wilson.
 
Nigerians are accustomed to seeing policemen at every junction of our cities. And when they stay-away, walkout or slowdown in subtle protest, we tend to miss them – but for the wrong reasons. Legally, police don’t go on industrial action and the authority would always dismiss its likelihood. But police officers can scale down operations as we have lately seen few policemen protecting only critical facilities, and responding to major security issues alone.   To enable commenting and other interactive features, please switch to the more advanced .